ent-RMCArmourM4TSEPAChief-name = M4 pattern inspector TSEPA armour
ent-RMCArmourM4TSEPAChief-desc = A modified variant of the M4 TSEPA armour to have the additional riot plating returned, featuring a golden insignia on the chestplate.

ent-RMCArmourM4TSEPA-name = M4 pattern light TSEPA armour
ent-RMCArmourM4TSEPA-desc = A modified variant of the M4R armor, stripped of additional riot plating for civilian officer use. A 'TSEPA' badge is sewn into the chestplate.

ent-RMCArmorVestTSEPA-name = TSEPA armored vest
ent-RMCArmorVestTSEPA-desc = An TSEPA armored vest that protects against some damage.

ent-RMCJacketParaCombatJacket-name = paramarine combat jacket
ent-RMCJacketParaCombatJacket-desc = A rugged, all-weather combat jacket issued to the RCM's Paramarine regiments. Designed for versatility, it serves as both a field garment and a lightweight layer of protection. Reinforced with ballistic fibers and treated for weather resistance, it offers limited defense against shrapnel and small arms fire while keeping Paramarines comfortable in harsh conditions. Its deep green color and durable fabric make it a staple for both active deployment and off-duty wear.

ent-RMCJacketParaCOJacket-name = paramarine commanding officer’s service jacket
ent-RMCJacketParaCOJacket-desc = A service jacket typically worn by Commanding Officers of the RCM's Paramarine regiments. Reinforced with lightweight Kevlar shards, it offers limited protection against stabbing weapons and small arms fire while maintaining a formal yet practical design for leadership in the field.

